introduction: This video discusses the potential of quantum computers to solve optimization problems and the interactive aspect of quantum computing. It also explores the challenges in understanding the noise and lint in quantum systems and the high energy part of the spectrum. The panelists also touch on the interactive protocols used in quantum computing and the balance between quick readout and decoherence. The video also highlights the challenges in error correction and feedback.

sections.title: Section 1: Quantum Computing and Optimization Problems
content: Discussion of the potential of quantum computers to solve optimization problems such as factoring and well-defined computational problems.
Exploration of the interactive aspect of quantum computing, where the question is about finding the shift in resonance frequency.
Challenges in understanding the noise and lint in quantum systems.
Examination of the high energy part of the spectrum and its relationship to the experiment and readout.
topics: High Energy Part of the Spectrum

sections.title: Section 2: Interactive Protocols in Quantum Computing
content: Exploration of the interactive protocols used in quantum computing.
Discussion of the balance between quick readout and decoherence.
Examination of the challenges in error correction and feedback.
Presentation of the complexity of the systems and the need for measurement at the end.
